begin_memory_text: My chat partner and I spoke about basic “getting to know you” questions. My partner shared that this was his first Prolific video chat. I shared with him about my previous experiences.
middle_memory_text: We spoke about our jobs and hobbies and interests during the middle of the conversation. The hobby I mentioned was sewing. The hobby my partner mentioned was geocaching.
end_memory_text: By the end of the conversation, we talked about how technology is changing how we view jobs and the arts during a pandemic. We talked about theatre and how actors memorize lines.
rest_of_day_open: I plan to work from home the rest of this week. I get a lot of enjoyment out of my job, which is a small sewing and alterations business, and I am looking forward to working on various sewing projects and new designs. I don’t currently have any social plans with family or friends, so I may feel lonely.
critical_positive: This conversation did not flow well at all. However, to keep things flowing, I tried to ask questions about my partner so he could talk about himself, which seemed to be the only topic he was interested in. He wasn’t openly hostile, so I suppose that is a positive aspect.
critical_negative: This was not the most pleasant or naturally-flowing conversation. My partner sat in silence, waiting for me to lead and initiate each conversation. My partner frequently interrupted me, whether I was asking a question or bringing up a new topic. He did not seem interested in anything I had to say, and he only asked me questions when prompted.

begin_memory_text: We talked about the weather. He asked me how it was where I lived. I asked him how it was where he lived. The air quality around him was not the best, but he seemed to be doing all right.
middle_memory_text: We talked about art. He enjoys sewing and seems to be good at it. I mentioned my interest in ceramics, but that I have never been that great at drawing. He understood that.
end_memory_text: We talked about teaching and how that is difficult to do from home. We also discussed how different jobs might be affected by the pandemic with some being better done from home then others.
rest_of_day_open: I think it will go all right. There isn't much of it left, but I have some plane for the reminder of the weekend. I am going to help with some yardwork after I finish this survey. Then maybe go on a bike ride as the weather is gorgeous at the moment.
critical_positive: We hit it off pretty well I think. I sometimes interrupt and talk over people, but that didn't happen in this case. We had some stuff in common that made conversing easier. He had done this before, so he knew how to make the conversation flow from topic to topic.
critical_negative: Pretty much nothing didn't work well between me and my conversation partner. There were a couple of awkward pauses, but that can happen in every conversation. The silences were never that dramatic or uncomfortable. It took a few seconds for the conversation to start flowing at the beginning. That didn't last long though.
